Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of opportunistic scheduling schemes in multiuser MIMO-SDMA downlink systems with linear combining. This involves the study of signal-to-interference-noise ratio (SINR) and effective SINR, which are key concepts in information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also utilizes extreme value theory, which is a statistical method commonly used in machine learning (cs.SI) and applied mathematics (cs.MA). Finally, the paper deals with MIMO-SDMA systems, which are a subfield of multimedia communications (cs.MM).
